      "author": "github-actions[bot]",
      "description": "I got rid of the build in option to open articles directly inside of obsidian. It just wasn't easy to get right and there were a lot of problems (e.g. #15). Luckily I found the amazing Surfing plugin which basically does what I was looking for! The Wikipedia Search plugin now integrates with the Surfing plugin. It provides the code to open the Wikipedia websites directly in obsidian. Just install it and you're ready to go! Trust me this is the better way. Of course I could have copied their awesome implementation but there really is no point and I think the plugin generally makes your life easier.",
